    79Ôćĺ## Recommended: Use `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`
    80Ôćĺ
    81ÔćĺAs part of `neverthrow`s [bounty program](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/issues/314), user [mdbetancourt](https://github.com/mdbetancourt) created [`eslint-plugin-neverthrow`](https://github.com/mdbetancourt/eslint-plugin-neverthrow) to ensure that errors are not gone unhandled.
   100Ôćĺ## Top-Level API
   101Ôćĺ
   102Ôćĺ`neverthrow` exposes the following:
   139Ôćĺ## API Documentation
   140Ôćĺ
   141Ôćĺ### Synchronous API (`Result`)
   143Ôćĺ#### `ok`
   144Ôćĺ
   145ÔćĺConstructs an `Ok` variant of `Result`
   168Ôćĺ#### `err`
   169Ôćĺ
   170ÔćĺConstructs an `Err` variant of `Result`
   193Ôćĺ#### `Result.isOk` (method)
   194Ôćĺ
   195ÔćĺReturns `true` if the result is an `Ok` variant
   207Ôćĺ#### `Result.isErr` (method)
   208Ôćĺ
   209ÔćĺReturns `true` if the result is an `Err` variant
   221Ôćĺ#### `Result.map` (method)
   222Ôćĺ
   223ÔćĺMaps a `Result<T, E>` to `Result<U, E>` by applying a function to a contained `Ok` value, leaving an `Err` value untouched.
   259Ôćĺ#### `Result.mapErr` (method)
   260Ôćĺ
   261ÔćĺMaps a `Result<T, E>` to `Result<T, F>` by applying a function to a contained `Err` value, leaving an `Ok` value untouched.
   297Ôćĺ#### `Result.unwrapOr` (method)
   298Ôćĺ
   299ÔćĺUnwrap the `Ok` value, or return the default if there is an `Err`
   323Ôćĺ#### `Result.andThen` (method)
   324Ôćĺ
   325ÔćĺSame idea as `map` above. Except you must return a new `Result`.
   384Ôćĺ#### `Result.asyncAndThen` (method)
   385Ôćĺ
   386ÔćĺSame idea as [`andThen` above](#resultandthen-method), except you must return a new `ResultAsync`.
   404Ôćĺ#### `Result.orElse` (method)
   405Ôćĺ
   406ÔćĺTakes an `Err` value and maps it to a `Result<T, SomeNewType>`. This is useful for error recovery.
   445Ôćĺ#### `Result.match` (method)
   446Ôćĺ
   447ÔćĺGiven 2 functions (one for the `Ok` variant and one for the `Err` variant) execute the function that matches the `Result` variant.
   514Ôćĺ#### `Result.asyncMap` (method)
   515Ôćĺ
   516ÔćĺSimilar to `map` except for two things:
   551Ôćĺ#### `Result.andTee` (method)
   552Ôćĺ
   553ÔćĺTakes a `Result<T, E>` and lets the original `Result<T, E>` pass through regardless the result of the passed-in function.
   598Ôćĺ#### `Result.orTee` (method)
   599Ôćĺ
   600ÔćĺLike `andTee` for the error track. Takes a `Result<T, E>` and lets the `Err` value pass through regardless the result of the passed-in function.
   645Ôćĺ#### `Result.andThrough` (method)
   646Ôćĺ
   647ÔćĺSimilar to `andTee` except for:
   692Ôćĺ#### `Result.asyncAndThrough` (method)
   693Ôćĺ
   694ÔćĺSimilar to `andThrough` except you must return a ResultAsync. 
   728Ôćĺ#### `Result.fromThrowable` (static class method)
   729Ôćĺ
   730Ôćĺ> Although Result is not an actual JS class, the way that `fromThrowable` has been implemented requires that you call `fromThrowable` as though it were a static method on `Result`. See examples below.
   761Ôćĺ#### `Result.combine` (static class method)
   762Ôćĺ
   763Ôćĺ> Although Result is not an actual JS class, the way that `combine` has been implemented requires that you call `combine` as though it were a static method on `Result`. See examples below.
   814Ôćĺ#### `Result.combineWithAllErrors` (static class method)
   815Ôćĺ
   816Ôćĺ> Although Result is not an actual JS class, the way that `combineWithAllErrors` has been implemented requires that you call `combineWithAllErrors` as though it were a static method on `Result`. See examples below.
   852Ôćĺ#### `Result.safeUnwrap()`
   853Ôćĺ
   854Ôćĺ**Deprecated**. You don't need to use this method anymore.
   863Ôćĺ### Asynchronous API (`ResultAsync`)
   864Ôćĺ
   865Ôćĺ#### `okAsync`
   892Ôćĺ#### `errAsync`
   893Ôćĺ
   894ÔćĺConstructs an `Err` variant of `ResultAsync`
   919Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.fromThrowable` (static class method)
   920Ôćĺ
   921ÔćĺSimilar to [Result.fromThrowable](#resultfromthrowable-static-class-method), but for functions that return a `Promise`.
   960Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.fromPromise` (static class method)
   961Ôćĺ
   962ÔćĺTransforms a `PromiseLike<T>` (that may throw) into a `ResultAsync<T, E>`.
   996Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.fromSafePromise` (static class method)
   997Ôćĺ
   998ÔćĺSame as `ResultAsync.fromPromise` except that it does not handle the rejection of the promise. **Ensure you know what you're doing, otherwise a thrown exception within this promise will cause ResultAsync to reject, instead of resolve to a Result.**
  1041Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.map` (method)
  1042Ôćĺ
  1043ÔćĺMaps a `ResultAsync<T, E>` to `ResultAsync<U, E>` by applying a function to a contained `Ok` value, leaving an `Err` value untouched.
  1087Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.mapErr` (method)
  1088Ôćĺ
  1089ÔćĺMaps a `ResultAsync<T, E>` to `ResultAsync<T, F>` by applying a function to a contained `Err` value, leaving an `Ok` value untouched.
  1142Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.unwrapOr` (method)
  1143Ôćĺ
  1144ÔćĺUnwrap the `Ok` value, or return the default if there is an `Err`.  
  1166Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.andThen` (method)
  1167Ôćĺ
  1168ÔćĺSame idea as `map` above. Except the applied function must return a `Result` or `ResultAsync`.
  1223Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.orElse` (method)
  1224Ôćĺ
  1225ÔćĺTakes an `Err` value and maps it to a `ResultAsync<T, SomeNewType>`. This is useful for error recovery.
  1241Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.match` (method)
  1242Ôćĺ
  1243ÔćĺGiven 2 functions (one for the `Ok` variant and one for the `Err` variant) execute the function that matches the `ResultAsync` variant.
  1283Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.andTee` (method)
  1284Ôćĺ
  1285ÔćĺTakes a `ResultAsync<T, E>` and lets the original `ResultAsync<T, E>` pass through regardless 
  1330Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.orTee` (method)
  1331Ôćĺ
  1332ÔćĺLike `andTee` for the error track. Takes a `ResultAsync<T, E>` and lets the original `Err` value pass through regardless 
  1377Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.andThrough` (method)
  1378Ôćĺ
  1379Ôćĺ
  1380ÔćĺSimilar to `andTee` except for:
  1425Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.combine` (static class method)
  1426Ôćĺ
  1427ÔćĺCombine lists of `ResultAsync`s.
  1475Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.combineWithAllErrors` (static class method)
  1476Ôćĺ
  1477ÔćĺLike `combine` but without short-circuiting. Instead of just the first error value, you get a list of all error values of the input result list.
  1509Ôćĺ#### `ResultAsync.safeUnwrap()`
  1510Ôćĺ
  1511Ôćĺ**Deprecated**. You don't need to use this method anymore.
  1519Ôćĺ### Utilities
  1520Ôćĺ
  1521Ôćĺ#### `fromThrowable`
  1528Ôćĺ#### `fromAsyncThrowable`
  1529Ôćĺ
  1530ÔćĺTop level export of `ResultAsync.fromThrowable`.
  1535Ôćĺ#### `fromPromise`
  1536Ôćĺ
  1537ÔćĺTop level export of `ResultAsync.fromPromise`.
  1542Ôćĺ#### `fromSafePromise`
  1543Ôćĺ
  1544ÔćĺTop level export of `ResultAsync.fromSafePromise`.
  1549Ôćĺ#### `safeTry`
  1550Ôćĺ
  1551ÔćĺUsed to implicitly return errors and reduce boilerplate.
  1633Ôćĺ### Testing
  1634Ôćĺ
  1635Ôćĺ`Result` instances have two unsafe methods, aptly called `_unsafeUnwrap` and `_unsafeUnwrapErr` which **should only be used in a test environment**.
  1673Ôćĺ## A note on the Package Name
  1674Ôćĺ
  1675ÔćĺAlthough the package is called `neverthrow`, please don't take this literally. I am simply encouraging the developer to think a bit more about the ergonomics and usage of whatever software they are writing.
  1681Ôćĺ### License
  1682Ôćĺ
  1683ÔćĺThe neverthrow project is available as open source under the terms of the [MIT license](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/blob/master/LICENSE).
